  <section id=3D"unit-testing-in-esp32">
<h1>Unit Testing in ESP32<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espre=
ssif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#unit-t=
esting-in-esp32" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h1>
<p><a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/proje=
cts/esp-idf/zh_CN/v6.0.2/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html">[=E4=B8=AD=E6=96=
=87]</a></p>
<p>ESP-IDF provides the following methods to test software.</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>Target based tests using a central unit test application which runs =
on the esp32. These tests use the <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.throwtheswitch.org/unity">Unity</a> unit test framework. They ca=
n be integrated into an ESP-IDF component by placing them in the component'=
s <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">test</sp=
an></code> subdirectory. This document mainly introduces this target based =
tests.</p></li>
<li><p>Linux-host based unit tests in which part of the hardware can be abs=
tracted via mocks. Currently, Linux-host based tests are still under develo=
pment and only a small fraction of IDF components support them. More inform=
ation on running IDF applications on the host can be found here: <a class=
=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf=
/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/host-apps.html"><span class=3D"doc">Running App=
lications on the Host Machine</span></a>.</p></li>
</ul>
<section id=3D"normal-test-cases">
<h2>Normal Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressif=
.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#normal-tes=
t-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>Unit tests are located in the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslat=
e"><span class=3D"pre">test</span></code> subdirectory of a component. Test=
s are written in C, and a single C source file can contain multiple test ca=
ses. Test files start with the word "test".</p>
<p>Each test file should include the <code class=3D"docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">unity.h</span></code> header and the header for =
the C module to be tested.</p>
<p>Tests are added in a function in the C file as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-c notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=3D"=
codecell0"><span></span><span class=3D"n">TEST_CASE</span><span class=3D"p"=
>(</span><span class=3D"s">"test name"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span><spa=
n class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s">"[module name]"</span><span class=
=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">        </span><span class=3D"c1">// Add test here</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell0">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>The first argument is a descriptive name for the test.</p></li>
<li><p>The second argument is an identifier in square brackets. Identifiers=
 are used to group related test, or tests with specific properties.</p></li=
>
</ul>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>There is no need to add a main function with <code class=3D"docutils lit=
eral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">UNITY_BEGIN()</span></code> and <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=E2=80=8BUNITY_=
END()</span></code> in each test case. <code class=3D"docutils literal notr=
anslate"><span class=3D"pre">unity_platform.c</span></code> will run <code =
class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">UNITY_BEGIN()</s=
pan></code> autonomously, and run the test cases, then call <code class=3D"=
docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=E2=80=8BUNITY_END()</spa=
n></code>.</p>
</div>
<p>The <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tes=
t</span></code> subdirectory should contain a <a class=3D"reference interna=
l" href=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-=
guides/build-system.html#component-directories"><span class=3D"std std-ref"=
>component CMakeLists.txt</span></a>, since they are themselves components =
(i.e., a test component). ESP-IDF uses the Unity test framework located in =
the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">unity<=
/span></code> component. Thus, each test component should specify the <code=
 class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">unity</span></c=
ode> component as a component requirement using the <code class=3D"docutils=
 literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">REQUIRES</span></code> argument. =
Normally, components <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.e=
spressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/build-system.html#=
cmake-file-globbing"><span class=3D"std std-ref">should list their sources =
manually</span></a>; for component tests however, this requirement is relax=
ed and the use of the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">SRC_DIRS</span></code> argument in <code class=3D"docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">idf_component_register</span></code> i=
s advised.</p>
<p>Overall, the minimal <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span =
class=3D"pre">test</span></code> subdirectory <code class=3D"docutils liter=
al notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">CMakeLists.txt</span></code> file shoul=
d contain the following:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-cmake notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=
=3D"codecell1"><span></span><span class=3D"nb">idf_component_register</span=
><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s">SRC_DIRS</span><span class=3D"=
w"> </span><span class=3D"s2">"."</span>
<span class=3D"w">                       </span><span class=3D"s">INCLUDE_D=
IRS</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s2">"."</span>
<span class=3D"w">                       </span><span class=3D"s">REQUIRES<=
/span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s">unity</span><span class=
=3D"p">)</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell1">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>See <a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"http://www.throwtheswitch.or=
g/unity">http://www.throwtheswitch.org/unity</a> for more information about=
 writing tests in Unity.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"multi-device-test-cases">
<h2>Multi-device Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.esp=
ressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#mult=
i-device-test-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>The normal test cases will be executed on one DUT (Device Under Test). H=
owever, components that require some form of communication (e.g., GPIO, SPI=
) require another device to communicate with, thus cannot be tested through=
 normal test cases. Multi-device test cases involve writing multiple test f=
unctions, and running them on multiple DUTs.</p>
<p>The following is an example of a multi-device test case:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-c notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre id=3D"=
codecell2"><span></span><span class=3D"kt">void</span><span class=3D"w"> </=
span><span class=3D"nf">gpio_master_test</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">gpio_config_t</span><span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">slave_config</span><span class=3D"w"> <=
/span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"=
p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">            </span><span class=3D"p">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">pin_bit_mask</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</=
span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"w"=
> </span><span class=3D"o">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span c=
lass=3D"n">MASTER_GPIO_PIN</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"w">            </span><span class=3D"p">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">mode</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">GPIO_MODE_INPUT</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"p">};</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">gpio_config</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"o">&amp;</span><span class=3D"n">slave_confi=
g</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">unity_wait_for_signal</span>=
<span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s">"output high level"</span><span=
 class=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">TEST_ASSERT</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">gpio_get_level</span><span class=3D"p">(<=
/span><span class=3D"n">MASTER_GPIO_PIN</span><span class=3D"p">)</span><sp=
an class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </=
span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>

<span class=3D"kt">void</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"nf">=
gpio_slave_test</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">gpio_config_t</span><span cl=
ass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">master_config</span><span class=3D"w"> =
</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D=
"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">            </span><span class=3D"p">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">pin_bit_mask</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</=
span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"w"=
> </span><span class=3D"o">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span c=
lass=3D"n">SLAVE_GPIO_PIN</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"w">            </span><span class=3D"p">.</span><span class=
=3D"n">mode</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">GPIO_MODE_OUTPUT</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"p">};</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">gpio_config</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"o">&amp;</span><span class=3D"n">master_conf=
ig</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">gpio_set_level</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">SLAVE_GPIO_PIN</span><span class=3D"p"=
>,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=
=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"n">unity_send_signal</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"s">"output high level"</span><span cla=
ss=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>

<span class=3D"n">TEST_CASE_MULTIPLE_DEVICES</span><span class=3D"p">(</spa=
n><span class=3D"s">"gpio multiple devices test example"</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"s">"[driver]"</span=
><span class=3D"p">,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">gpio=
_master_test</span><span class=3D"p">,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><spa=
n class=3D"n">gpio_slave_test</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell2">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>The macro <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pr=
e">TEST_CASE_MULTIPLE_DEVICES</span></code> is used to declare a multi-devi=
ce test case.</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>The first argument is test case name.</p></li>
<li><p>The second argument is test case description.</p></li>
<li><p>From the third argument, up to 5 test functions can be defined, each=
 function will be the entry point of tests running on each DUT.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Running test cases from different DUTs could require synchronizing betwe=
en DUTs. We provide <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span clas=
s=3D"pre">unity_wait_for_signal</span></code> and <code class=3D"docutils l=
iteral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">unity_send_signal</span></code> to =
support synchronizing with UART. As the scenario in the above example, the =
slave should get GPIO level after master set level. DUT UART console will p=
rompt and user interaction is required:</p>
<p>DUT1 (master) console:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
id=3D"codecell3"><span></span>Waiting for signal: [output high level]!
Please press "Enter" key to once any board send this signal.
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell3">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>DUT2 (slave) console:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
id=3D"codecell4"><span></span>Send signal: [output high level]!
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell4">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>Once the signal is sent from DUT2, you need to press "Enter" on DUT1, th=
en DUT1 unblocks from <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">unity_wait_for_signal</span></code> and starts to change GPIO l=
evel.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"multi-stage-test-cases">
<h2>Multi-stage Test Cases<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espr=
essif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#multi=
-stage-test-cases" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>The normal test cases are expected to finish without reset (or only need=
 to check if reset happens). Sometimes we expect to run some specific tests=
 after certain kinds of reset. For example, we want to test if the reset re=
ason is correct after a wake up from deep sleep. We need to create a deep-s=
leep reset first and then check the reset reason. To support this, we can d=
efine multi-stage test cases, to group a set of test functions:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
id=3D"codecell5"><span></span><span class=3D"n">static</span> <span class=
=3D"n">void</span> <span class=3D"n">trigger_deepsleep</span><span class=3D=
"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">void</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
    <span class=3D"n">esp_sleep_enable_timer_wakeup</span><span class=3D"p"=
>(</span><span class=3D"mi">2000</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
    <span class=3D"n">esp_deep_sleep_start</span><span class=3D"p">();</spa=
n>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>

<span class=3D"n">void</span> <span class=3D"n">check_deepsleep_reset_reaso=
n</span><span class=3D"p">()</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
    <span class=3D"n">soc_reset_reason_t</span> <span class=3D"n">reason</s=
pan> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">esp_rom_get_reset_reaso=
n</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D=
"p">);</span>
    <span class=3D"n">TEST_ASSERT</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span cla=
ss=3D"n">reason</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">RE=
SET_REASON_CORE_DEEP_SLEEP</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>

<span class=3D"n">TEST_CASE_MULTIPLE_STAGES</span><span class=3D"p">(</span=
><span class=3D"s2">"reset reason check for deepsleep"</span><span class=3D=
"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s2">"[esp32]"</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> =
<span class=3D"n">trigger_deepsleep</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span =
class=3D"n">check_deepsleep_reset_reason</span><span class=3D"p">);</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell5">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<p>Multi-stage test cases present a group of test functions to users. It ne=
eds user interactions (select cases and select different stages) to run the=
 case.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"tests-for-different-targets">
<h2>Tests For Different Targets<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs=
.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#=
tests-for-different-targets" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81<=
/a></h2>
<p>Some tests (especially those related to hardware) cannot run on all targ=
ets. Below is a guide how to make your unit tests run on only specified tar=
gets.</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic">
<li><p>Wrap your test code by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate">=
<span class=3D"pre">!(TEMPORARY_)DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS()</span></code> macro=
s and place them either in the original test file, or separate the code int=
o files grouped by functions, but make sure all these files will be process=
ed by the compiler. E.g.:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
id=3D"codecell6"><span></span><span class=3D"c1">#if !TEMPORARY_DISABLED_FO=
R_TARGETS(ESP32, ESP8266)</span>
<span class=3D"n">TEST_CASE</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"=
s2">"a test that is not ready for esp32 and esp8266 yet"</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s2">"[]"</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
<span class=3D"c1">#endif //!TEMPORARY_DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS(ESP32, ESP8266)=
</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell6">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Once you need one of the tests to be compiled on a specified target, jus=
t modify the targets in the disabled list. It's more encouraged to use some=
 general conception that can be described in <code class=3D"docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">soc_caps.h</span></code> to control the =
disabling of tests. If this is done but some of the tests are not ready yet=
, use both of them (and remove <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">!(TEMPORARY_)DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS()</span></code> late=
r). E.g.:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
id=3D"codecell7"><span></span><span class=3D"c1">#if SOC_SDIO_SLAVE_SUPPORT=
ED</span>
<span class=3D"c1">#if !TEMPORARY_DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS(ESP64)</span>
<span class=3D"n">TEST_CASE</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"=
s2">"a sdio slave tests that is not ready for esp64 yet"</span><span class=
=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"s2">"[sdio_slave]"</span><span class=3D"p">)=
</span>
<span class=3D"p">{</span>
    <span class=3D"o">//</span><span class=3D"n">available</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"k">for</span> <span class=3D"n">esp32</span> <span class=3D"n">now</s=
pan><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"ow">and</span> <span class=3D=
"n">will</span> <span class=3D"n">be</span> <span class=3D"n">available</sp=
an> <span class=3D"k">for</span> <span class=3D"n">esp64</span> <span class=
=3D"ow">in</span> <span class=3D"n">the</span> <span class=3D"n">future</sp=
an>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
<span class=3D"c1">#endif //!TEMPORARY_DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS(ESP64)</span>
<span class=3D"c1">#endif //SOC_SDIO_SLAVE_SUPPORTED</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell7">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple" start=3D"2">
<li><p>For test code that you are 100% for sure that will not be supported =
(e.g., no peripheral at all), use <code class=3D"docutils literal notransla=
te"><span class=3D"pre">DISABLED_FOR_TARGETS</span></code>; for test code t=
hat should be disabled temporarily, or due to lack of runners, etc., use <c=
ode class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">TEMPORARY_DI=
SABLED_FOR_TARGETS</span></code>.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Some old ways of disabling unit tests for targets, that have obvious dis=
advantages, are deprecated:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>DON'T put the test code under <code class=3D"docutils literal notran=
slate"><span class=3D"pre">test/target</span></code> folder and use CMakeLi=
sts.txt to choose one of the target folder. This is prevented because test =
code is more likely to be reused than the implementations. If you put somet=
hing into <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">=
test/esp32</span></code> just to avoid building it on esp32s2, it's hard to=
 make the code tidy if you want to enable the test again on esp32s3.</p></l=
i>
<li><p>DON'T use <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">CONFIG_IDF_TARGET_xxx</span></code> macros to disable the test ite=
ms any more. This makes it harder to track disabled tests and enable them a=
gain. Also, a black-list style <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">#if</span> <span class=3D"pre">!disabled</span></code>=
 is preferred to white-list style <code class=3D"docutils literal notransla=
te"><span class=3D"pre">#if</span> <span class=3D"pre">CONFIG_IDF_TARGET_xx=
x</span></code>, since you will not silently disable cases when new targets=
 are added in the future. But for test implementations, it's allowed to use=
 <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">#if</span=
> <span class=3D"pre">CONFIG_IDF_TARGET_xxx</span></code> to pick one of th=
e implementation code.</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Test item: some items that will be performed on some targets, but sk=
ipped on other targets. E.g.</p>
<p>There are three test items SD 1-bit, SD 4-bit and SDSPI. For ESP32-S2, w=
hich doesn't have SD host, among the tests only SDSPI is enabled on ESP32-S=
2.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Test implementation: some code will always happen, but in different =
ways. E.g.</p>
<p>There is no SDIO PKT_LEN register on ESP8266. If you want to get the len=
gth from the slave as a step in the test process, you can have different im=
plementation code protected by <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"=
><span class=3D"pre">#if</span> <span class=3D"pre">CONFIG_IDF_TARGET_</spa=
n></code> reading in different ways.</p>
<p>But please avoid using <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><spa=
n class=3D"pre">#else</span></code> macro. When new target is added, the te=
st case will fail at building stage, so that the maintainer will be aware o=
f this, and choose one of the implementations explicitly.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id=3D"building-unit-test-apps">
<h2>Building Unit Test Apps<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.esp=
ressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#buil=
ding-unit-test-apps" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<p>Follow the setup instructions in the top-level esp-idf README. Make sure=
 that <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">IDF_=
PATH</span></code> environment variable is set to point to the path of esp-=
idf top-level directory.</p>
<p>Change into the test app directory to configure and build it:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">idf=
.py</span> <span class=3D"pre">menuconfig</span></code> - configure unit te=
st app.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">idf=
.py</span> <span class=3D"pre">build</span></code> - build unit test app.</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p>When the build finishes, it will print instructions for flashing the chi=
p. You can simply run <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span cl=
ass=3D"pre">idf.py</span> <span class=3D"pre">flash</span></code> to flash =
all build output.</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"running-unit-tests">
<h2>Running Unit Tests<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://docs.espressi=
f.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/api-guides/unit-tests.html#running-u=
nit-tests" title=3D"Permalink to this heading">=EF=83=81</a></h2>
<div class=3D"admonition note">
<p class=3D"admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>We also provide the pytest-based framework <a class=3D"reference externa=
l" href=3D"https://github.com/espressif/pytest-embedded">pytest-embedded</a=
> to help make running unit-tests more convenient and efficient. If you nee=
d to run tests in CI or run multiple tests in a row we recommend checking o=
ut this project. For more information see <a class=3D"reference external" h=
ref=3D"https://docs.espressif.com/projects/pytest-embedded/en/latest/">Pyte=
st-embedded Docs</a> and <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://do=
cs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/stable/esp32/contribute/esp-idf-tests-=
with-pytest.html"><span class=3D"doc">ESP-IDF Tests with Pytest Guide</span=
></a>.</p>
</div>
